sudo ln -s /etc/opt/chrome /etc/chromium

2 screens - go to displays, sticky edges, change to off.
4 desktops - appearance -> behaviour -> Enable workspaces

Hide "Public" folder: go to ~/.config/user-dirs.dirs and edit.
Make them all look like this: XDG_TEMPLATES_DIR="$HOME"

To move partition, follow instructions at: https://help.ubuntu.com/community/Partitioning/Home/Moving
To get the UUID number:
sudo blkid
To edit the boot folder thingy:\\
sudo gedit /etc/fstab
Add in two lines with something like:
UUID=690f1cf2-b5f6-4230-9cf2-58d99448624d	/home	ext4	defaults	0	2
#You might want to do this in two parts, to check that Videos folder has been created. Also, check what the name of your user is.
UUID=58fd507a-9a64-4c80-9c1a-0ffe680262c7	/home/max/Videos	ext3	defaults	0	2
Add a # in front of the floppy disk line


