install flash:
sudo gedit /etc/apt/sources.list
uncomment the following 2 lines:
deb http://archive.canonical.com/ubuntu trusty partner
deb-src http://archive.canonical.com/ubuntu trusty partner
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install adobe-flashplugin

for skype
Download from website
If it doesn't work straight away, try
sudo dpkg --add-architecture i386
and install synaptic -> edit -> fix broken packages.


to stop mathematica from making it's "Wolfram Mathematica" folder, edit ~/.Mathematica/Kernel/init.m and add the line:
With[{dir = $HomeDirectory <> "/Wolfram Mathematica"},
  If[DirectoryQ[dir], DeleteDirectory[dir]]
]


remove keychain:
Password and Encryption Keys, right click on 'Login' select change password to nothing.


install .deb
sudo dpkg -i packagename.deb

install .sh
sudo chmod +x file.sh
sudo ./file.sh

install .tar.gz or .tar.bz2
extract the file
usually a .sh file - read install/readme files


change default folder for anki - 
cd /usr/share/anki/aqt
sudo gedit profiles.py
and change the following line:
return os.path.expanduser("~/Anki")
to
return os.path.expanduser("~/misc/Anki")


To move the chrome window closer/minimiser, go to chrome settings, tick "use system title bar and borders"
And then, use in terminal:
gconftool-2 --set /apps/metacity/general/button_layout --type string "close,minimize,maximize:"

Add video card driver - Software and updates -> additional drivers
Add add blocker

settings -> language support
Time and Date Settings, modify accordingly.
To get week starting on monday:
sudo gedit /etc/default/locale
ADD: LC_TIME="en_GB.UTF-8"
To change date format:
gsettings set com.canonical.indicator.datetime time-format "'custom'"
gsettings set com.canonical.indicator.datetime custom-time-format "'%a %d %b %Y, %I:%M:%S %p'"


